comments:
Created 1894 out of the parish of Brampton Bierlow. Renamed 19.7.1897 
    to become the parish of Brampton Bierlow.

Abolished 1894 to become the separate parishes of Brampton and 
    West Melton.

Created 19.7.1897 by renaming the parish of Brampton. See also 
    Table 2, note (i).
Abolished 1.4.1923 and added to the parish of Thurcroft.

Abolished 1.4.1936 and divided between the parishes of Rotherham, 
    Rawmarsh and Wentworth.

Abolished 1894 and divided between the parishes of Rotherham and 
    Wentworh.
Abolished 1.4.1923 and added to the parish of Thurcroft.

Abolished 1.4.1974 and added to the Rotherham unparished area. See also Table 
    2, note (k).

That part which until 31.10.1901 formed parts of the parishes of 
    Catclffe and Tinsley. See also Table 2, note (f).

That part which until 1.4.1933 formed part of the parish of Tinsley. 
    See also Table 2, note (g).

Created 1.4.1923 from the parishes of Laughton-en-le-Morthen and 
    Brampton-en-le-Morthen. See also Table 2, note (i).

Abolished 1.4.1933 and added to the parish of Sheffield. 
    See also Table 2, notes (f) and (g).

Created 1894 from the part of the parish of Brampton Bierlow in 
    Wath upon Dearne Urban District. Abolished 1.4.1923 and added to the parish 
    of Wath upon Dearne.
